#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/async-defer-await.md
M|rules|title: Defer Await Until Needed
M|rules|impact: HIGH
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids blocking unused code paths
M|rules|tags: async, await, conditional, optimization
M|rules|Move `await` operations into the branches where they're actually used to avoid blocking code paths that don't need them.
M|rules|**Incorrect (blocks both branches):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|async function handleRequest(userId: string, skipProcessing: boolean) {
M|rules|const userData = await fetchUserData(userId)
M|rules|if (skipProcessing) {
M|rules|// Returns immediately but still waited for userData
M|rules|return { skipped: true }
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Only this branch uses userData
M|rules|return processUserData(userData)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (only blocks when needed):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|async function handleRequest(userId: string, skipProcessing: boolean) {
M|rules|if (skipProcessing) {
M|rules|// Returns immediately without waiting
M|rules|return { skipped: true }
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Fetch only when needed
M|rules|const userData = await fetchUserData(userId)
M|rules|return processUserData(userData)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Another example (early return optimization):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|// Incorrect: always fetches permissions
M|rules|async function updateResource(resourceId: string, userId: string) {
M|rules|const permissions = await fetchPermissions(userId)
M|rules|const resource = await getResource(resourceId)
M|rules|if (!resource) {
M|rules|return { error: 'Not found' }
M|rules|}
M|rules|if (!permissions.canEdit) {
M|rules|return { error: 'Forbidden' }
M|rules|}
M|rules|return await updateResourceData(resource, permissions)
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Correct: fetches only when needed
M|rules|async function updateResource(resourceId: string, userId: string) {
M|rules|const resource = await getResource(resourceId)
M|rules|if (!resource) {
M|rules|return { error: 'Not found' }
M|rules|}
M|rules|const permissions = await fetchPermissions(userId)
M|rules|if (!permissions.canEdit) {
M|rules|return { error: 'Forbidden' }
M|rules|}
M|rules|return await updateResourceData(resource, permissions)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|This optimization is especially valuable when the skipped branch is frequently taken, or when the deferred operation is expensive.
M|rules|For `await getFlag()` combined with a cheap synchronous guard (`flag && someCondition`), see [Check Cheap Conditions Before Async Flags](./async-cheap-condition-before-await.md).